# Installation
- `cd` into `install_scripts` and run all shell scripts

# Using Modules
- `module use modulefiles`, then `module purge` and `module refresh`
- `module avail` should now show the `cesm-prereqs` module containing ncurses and cshell
- See other relevant modules:
	- `hdf5-icc` (comes with Intel MPI and Intel ICC)
	- `hdf5-gcc` (comes with OpenMPI and GCC)
	- `lapack-gcc` (comes with CBLAS)
	- `mkl` (Intel MKL)

